    "body": "> This seems important. Thanks @citizen-stig for the reproduction example.\r\n> \r\n> There seems to be a limit in V8 that causes `JSON.stringify` to not work with large inputs. We might need to move from plain `JSON.parse`/`JSON.stringify` to some module for doing these operations with streams.\r\n\r\nThank you Franco for picking this up.\r\n\r\nI don't know internals of hardhat, but I've noticed that problem is not in single large smart contract, but combinations of them. So if one smart contract is removed, it will pass, even if this smart contract is not largers.\r\nMaybe batching stringification per smart contract might help and be good quick fix.",
